Functional and Non functional requirements

Requirement analysis is a crucial step in software development where the needs and expectations of users and stakeholders are identified
and documented. It ensures that the system being built will meet its intended goals and correct functionality.
Based on the requirements it is of two types:
1. Functional Requirments (defines What the system should perform)
2. Non Functional Requirements ( defines how the system should perform)

Functional Requirements :

-> It defines the specific features and operatios a system must perform to meet business and user needs.
-> They describe what the system do and how it interacts 
